article.headline: Penn State 68, Northwestern 55
article.story: STATE COLLEGE, Pa. (AP) -- Travis Parker and Geary Claxton each scored 14 points and Penn State took advantage of free-throw opportunities to defeat Northwestern 68-55 Saturday. The win assures the Nittany Lions (14-12, 6-9 Big Ten) of at least a .500 record following the Big Ten Tournament, strengthening their case for a bid to the National Invitation Tournament. Penn State scored 20 points from the free throw line (20-of-26), while Northwestern (13-13, 5-9) missed all three of its foul shots. Evan Seacat hit six 3-pointers for a career-high 18 points off the bench in the second half to pull the Wildcats within striking distance, but Mike Walker countered with nine straight points to fuel an 18-5 run that put the game out of reach. Penn State also got 11 points from Jamelle Cornley. Vedran Vukusic chipped in 15 for Northwestern. Penn State used its advantage in foul shots to pull away early, shooting 13-of-15 in the first half for a 35-25 lead at halftime.
